Anonymous Wed 10 Mar 2021 08:00:17 No.36964047 Report
Quoted By: >>36964136 >>36964168
>>36963428
I attempted to do a bunch or short pieces as exercises a long time ago.
If you want to write short, have an ending in mind. Some might say the shorter the piece, the harder it should impact. Another few sentences might have sold it better, but like you said - first real attempt.
No matter how short, there is still a conflict. And all flash is when you break it down is a short chapter. Whether you achieved that is up to you. I'd have balanced the setting and narration differently. I narrate the fuck out of first person. Third? Tell the setting, show the people. But the important point? Connection. Empathy. Two people meet. Fin, as the music scores say.

A tip going forward: one speaker per paragraph.
So
>“Oh, Absol, cool.” he said, voice still shaky.
>Her eyes lit up. “Yes! I love them so much.” she said.
>“Yeah, they’re, uh, cool. I had...Sapphire.”
>“So did I! The doctors...
Is more traditional.

And you're right. It's a start. That means #2 isn't your first.
